law.text:
Any function or activity of the Governor's Committee to Keep Maryland Beautiful is transferred to the Trust. These functions and activities include, by way of enumeration and not limitation:
Educating Maryland citizens and visitors in their individual responsibility in litter prevention and care of the out-of-doors through a two-fold approach:
Awareness-publicity through radio, TV, newspapers, and other public media;
Action-cleanup and beautification projects carried out by civic organizations, county committees, and community groups in cooperation with public agencies;
Efficient use of public and private funds spent on cleaning up highways, parks, beaches, and other public and private property;
Increasing beauty through stimulation of private business, community, and public planting projects;
Stimulating pride and appreciation for home, community, and State.
